Name: Celestial_Coordinates
Description: This class specifies right ascension and declination in a specific reference frame and coordinate system.

Name: reference_frame_id
Description: An abbreviation for the reference frame for corresponding vector components

Name: J2000
Description: The coordinates are given in the J2000 reference epoch and equinox.

Name: ICRF
Description: The coordinates are given in the International Celestial Reference Frame.

Name: coordinate_system_origin
Description: One of a set of predefined strings that indicates the origin of a coordinate system used for the association coordinates

Name: spacecraft
Description: The coordinate system origin is at the center of mass of the spacecraft.

Name: light_time_flag
Description: Flag indicating whether a light travel time correction has been applied to the associated values. A value of true" indicates it has been applied; "false" indicates no correction has been applied. "

Name: stellar_aberration_flag
Description: This flag indicates whether a correction for stellar aberration has been applied to the associated coordinates. A value of true" indicates that the correction has been applied; "false" indicates no correction for aberration has beem applied. "

Name: right_ascension
Description: Right ascension in the associated celestial reference frame and coordinate system

Name: declination
Description: Declination in the associated celestrial reference frame and coordinate system

Name: Display_Direction
Description: This class mimics the Display_Direction class in the Display dictionary. It's here until I figure out how to include that class directly.

Name: comment
Description: Free-format text for miscellaneous comments to the end user about the associated attributes or their values.

Name: horizontal_display_axis
Description: The horizontal_display_axis attribute identifies, by name, the axis of an Array (or Array subclass) that is intended to be displayed in the horizontal or sample" dimension on a display device. The value of this attribute must match the value of one
Value Type: axis_name attribute in an Axis_Array class of the associated Array. "

Name: horizontal_display_direction
Description: The horizontal_display_direction attribute specifies the direction across the screen of a display device that data along the horizontal axis of an Array is supposed to be displayed.

Name: Left to Right
Description:
The image should be drawn so that the (0,0) pixel is located on the
                    left edge of the displayed image, and subsequent columns should be
                    drawn to the right.

Name: Right to Left
Description:
The image should be drawn so that the (0,0) pixel is located on the
                    right edge of the displayed image, and subsequent columns should be
                    drawn to the left.

Name: vertical_display_axis
Description: The vertical_display_axis attribute identifies, by name, the axis of an Array (or Array subclass) that is intended to be displayed in the vertical or line" dimension on a display device. The value of this attribute must match the value of one
Value Type: axis_name attribute in an Axis_Array class of the associated Array. "

Name: vertical_display_direction
Description: The vertical_display_direction attribute specifies the direction along the screen of a display device that data along the vertical axis of an Array is supposed to be displayed.

Name: Top to Bottom
Description:
The image should be drawn so that the (0,0) pixel is located at 
                    the top of the displayed image, and subsequent rows are drawn 
                    downward.

Name: Bottom to Top
Description:
The image should be drawn so that the (0,0) pixel is located at
                    the bottom of the displayed image, and subsequent rows are drawn
                    upward.

Name: Target_Specification
Description: This class provides a number of ways to identify a single, specific target. In general, any or all of them may be used.

Name: target_name
Description: The name of the target of interest. For planets, minor planets, and similar observational targets, this should be a name string that includes at least two forms of identification whenever possible, to help with disambiguation in the archive indices.

Name: target_NAIF_ID
Description: The NAIF SPK-ID of the target body, if any

Name: target_LID
Description: The logical identifier (LID) in the PDS4 repository of a context object describing the target

Name: Illumination_Angles
Description: This class collects illumination angles relevant to the specified target.

Name: solar_elongation
Description: The angle between the line of sight to the center of the specified target in the associated image and the direction of the sun as seen by the observer [ Note: This definition is not sufficiently specific. ]

Name: phase_angle
Description: Angle, measured at the target, from the position of the source of illumination to the line of sight [Note: This definition is not sufficiently specific. It does not include direction of measurement or range of valid values. And the primary to secondary indication is a guess.]

Name: Target_Pole_Clock_Angle
Description: This class specifies a target and the clock angle for the positive rotation pole of that target as seen in the associated image, when it is properly displayed.

Name: body_positive_pole_clock_angle
Description: In the displayed image, the angle of the direction of the positive rotation pole of the associated body, measured at the center of the image, clockwise from the positive vertical

Name: Clock_Angles
Description: This class contains clock angles specifying key directions in the associated image when it is displayed correctly.

Name: celestial_north_clock_angle
Description: In the displayed image, the angle of the direction of the north celestial pole, measured at the center of the image, clockwise from the positive vertical

Name: ecliptic_north_clock_angle
Description: In the displayed image, the angle of the direction of the north ecliptic pole, measured at the center of the image, clockwise from the positive vertical

Name: sun_direction_clock_angle
Description: In the displayed image, the angle of the direction vector to the sun projected onto the plane of the image, measured at the center of the image, clockwise from the positive vertical

Name: Distances
Description: Various distance measurements relevant to the product observation

Name: spacecraft_geocentric_distance
Description: Distance from the center of the Earth to the center of mass of the spacecraft

Name: spacecraft_heliocentric_distance
Description: Distance from the center of the sun to the center of mass of the spacecraft

Name: Earth_Vectors
Description: This class collects vectors that have their origin at the center of mass of the Earth.

Name: Spacecraft_Vectors
Description: This class collects vectors with their origin at the center of mass of the spacecraft.

Name: Sun_Vectors
Description: This class collects vectors with their origin at the center of mass of the Sun.

Name: Image_Display_Geometry
Description: This class incorporates the Display Dictionary display class and includes orientation atttributes for key directions as they appear in the correctly displayed image.

Name: Spacecraft_Geometry
Description: This class combines a number of classes related to the geometry of a spacecraft-based observation.

Name: Geometry
Description: This master class contains all the geometry dictionary classes and should be included directly in observational product levels in the Mission_Area". "

Name: geometry_reference_time
Description: This is the UTC time at which all the geometric values following were calculated, unless an attribute within a class specifies otherwise.
